english:
  title: Remembering the Dwelling of Li the Hermit Scholar in Jiangnan
  author: Choi Gwang-yu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Once I visited the home of Lord Dai in Jiangnan—
    Before his gate, the empty river swallowed the dawn's crimson glow.
    Sitting beneath the moon, I poured the precious wine,
    And in spring's wandering, our orchid boat drifted through peach blossoms.
    In the courtyard, dewy lotus flowers bloomed red upon the stone steps,
    Beyond the window, clear mountains sent their emerald hue through the silk screen.
    Yet I only remember those old journeys, dreaming them night after night—
    While I, worn by the east wind, weep alone in the capital.
  footnotes:
    - Bamboo Leaf Wine (竹葉酒) was a celebrated liquor of ancient China, flavored with bamboo leaves and known for its excellence.
    - The 'orchid boat' (蘭舸) is a poetic name for a pleasure boat, often used in classical Chinese poetry to evoke elegance and leisure.
    - The final couplet shifts from memory to present sorrow, suggesting the poet's current exile or distance from such idyllic moments in Jiangnan.
